Durban - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal will for the second time, attempt to re-run its provincial conference which was declared null and void by the Pietermaritzburg High Court. Despite a rocky start, the conference finally got underway around 6:30pm. As delegates from across the province descend on the Durban University of Technology we take a look at the main players and why the conference is being re-run. Who are the main players?   How did we get here?        So what now?     Who else is expected to attend the conference?   Daily News